It's bit tricky-I also make a MMC5 homebrew(it'll take some time to finish) that also use ExRAM.<br />When you write to ExRAM, CPU(?) mirror $5000-$5FFF to $6000-$6FFFF.<br />In other words, you can see what you'v written at $6000-$6FFF, but changing those won't do anything.<p>Statistics: Posted by <a href="http://forums.nesdev.com/memberlist.php?mode=viewprofile&amp;u=4239">Denine</a> — Sun Jan 01, 2012 3:05 pm</p><hr />
